# zip_open: a file entry flagged as UTF-8 (general purpose bit 11) whose name
# is not valid UTF-8 must be rejected. Here the name is ED A0 80, the UTF-8
# encoding of the surrogate half U+D800, which is not a valid code point.
program tryopen
arguments -s test.zzip
file test.zzip incons-utf8-name-surrogate.zip
return 1
stdout
opening 'test.zzip' returned error Zip archive inconsistent: entry 0: invalid UTF-8 in filename
end-of-inline-data
stderr
1 errors
end-of-inline-data
